<item>
            <title>[LU-7772] catalogs shouldn&apos;t destroy plain llogs twice</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7772</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;if plain llog is found corrupted, then llog_process_thread() cancels all the remaining records which in turn causes destroy of the plain llog. but it&apos;s still referenced by the catalog in-core structure and llog_cat_close() may try to destroy it again causing a panic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
